Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{45%g}.

Halve any large cauliflower florets, then pop the @cauliflower florets{300%g} onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over the @ground cumin{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the cauliflower roasts, add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the mushrooms and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you don't like heat) and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{50%ml} for the sauce, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%can}, lentils and @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}. Stir to combine then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once the cauliflower is cooked, stir it through the sauce then remove from the heat.

> Add a splash more water if it's a little thick.

Increase the oven temperature to 220°C. Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir in half the chives.

Taste your filling and season if needed, then transfer to an appropriately-sized #ovenproof dish{} (we used 20x20cm for 2 people). Top with an even layer of mash and sprinkle over the cheese. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{10-15%minutes}. Serve with the remaining chives sprinkled over. Enjoy!